’m thinking about whether the test build agent generates config for native compile, and it likely includes the target even if it’s a test class. That seems okay, but I’m also looking at the dynamic coverage target and how it involves callsite origin. I shouldn’t overthink this. There’s a potential need for the current code FieldAccessorTable to statically initialize with DESCRIPTOR, and that TestProtoDescriptors has a FILE_DESCRIPTOR initialized. Alright, time to inspect file snippets and check the git diff.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_HeAS9t8igVq5HdW8xWqMJhyn|fc_019622ae838248cf0169f2b96d770c819c9fea969956f31ac2", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/DescriptorMessageInfoFactoryTest.java", "limit": 260}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_6wjvLGCzvGmDpXFIQDj9Np2L|fc_019622ae838248cf0169f2b96d771c819c945e2c4a04982e48", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git status --short && git diff -- tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/DescriptorMessageInfoFactoryTest.java", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 610, "output": 937, "cacheRead": 49152, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 50699, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777514845972, "responseId": "resp_019622ae838248cf0169f2b95e8d58819cbcab6e5164de969a"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_HeAS9t8igVq5HdW8xWqMJhyn|fc_019622ae838248cf0169f2b96d770c819c9fea969956f31ac2", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_kafka.kafka_clients;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport org.apache.kafka.shaded.com.google.protobuf.CodedInputStream;\nimport org.apache.kafka.shaded.com.google.protobuf.DescriptorProtos;\nimport org.apache.kafka.shaded.com.google.protobuf.Descriptors;\nimport org.apache.kafka.shaded.com.google.protobuf.ExtensionRegistryLite;\nimport org.apache.kafka.shaded.com.google.protobuf.GeneratedMessageV3;\nimport org.apache.kafka.shaded.com.google.protobuf.Message;\nimport org.apache.kafka.shaded.com.google.protobuf.UnknownFieldSet;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class DescriptorMessageInfoFactoryTest {\n    @Test\n    void buildsDescriptorBackedSchemaForOneofAndRepeatedMessageFields() throws Exception {\n        CoverageProbeMessage message = CoverageProbeMessage.getDefaultInstance();\n        CodedInputStream input = CodedInputStream.newInstance(new byte[0]);\n\n        message.mergeEmptyInputThroughGeneratedMessageSchema(input);\n\n        assertTrue(message.isInitialized());\n        assertSame(NestedMessage.getDefaultInstance(), message.getNestedValue());\n        assertEquals(0, message.getValuesCount());\n    }\n\n    public static final class CoverageProbeMessage extends GeneratedMessageV3 {\n        private static final Descriptors.Descriptor DESCRIPTOR = TestProtoDescriptors.messageDescriptor(\"CoverageProbe\");\n        private static final CoverageProbeMessage DEFAULT_INSTANCE = new CoverageProbeMessage();\n        private static final FieldAccessorTable FIELD_ACCESSOR_TABLE = new FieldAccessorTable(\n                DESCRIPTOR,\n                new String[] {\"NestedValue\", \"StringValue\", \"Values\", \"Kind\"});\n\n        @SuppressWarnings(\"unused\")\n        private int kindCase_;\n\n        @SuppressWarnings(\"unused\")\n        private Object kind_;\n\n        @Supp